

In infra folder : 

 1. In test directory > resources > wiremock  
 2. Create directory with your service and 2 sub directories 
    * _files with sub directory 
            * _responses 
    * mappings 
  where we regualiry have _proxy.json file 
  Sample : 
         {
        "name": "second-screen-service-proxy",
        "priority": 10,
        "request": {
        "urlPattern": ".*"
          },
        "response": {
        "proxyBaseUrl": "http://???:8080/"
          } 
         }


3. Modify POM to iniate docker image on new service.

                            <image>
                                    <alias>qa-automation.second-screen-wm</alias>
                                    <name>com.adswizz.domain.qa/qa-automation.second-screen-wm</name>
                                    <external>
                                        <type>properties</type>
                                        <prefix>docker.wm</prefix>
                                        <mode>override</mode>
                                    </external>
                                    <run>
                                        <namingStrategy>alias</namingStrategy>
                                        <network>
                                            <mode>custom</mode>
                                            <name>qa-automation-tests</name>
                                            <alias>qa-automation.second-screen-wm</alias>
                                        </network>
                                        <ports>
                                            <port>59104:9100</port>
                                        </ports>
                                        <wait>
                                            <time>5000</time>
                                        </wait>
                                        <log>
                                            <prefix>second-screen&gt;_</prefix>
                                            <color>yellow</color>
                                        </log>
                                        <volumes>
                                            <bind>
                                                <volume>
                                                    ${project.basedir}/src/test/resources/wiremock/second-screen/mappings:/servers/wiremock/mappings
                                                </volume>
                                                <volume>
                                                    ${project.basedir}/src/test/resources/wiremock/second-screen/__files:/servers/wiremock/__files
                                                </volume>
                                            </bind>
                                        </volumes>
                                    </run>
                                </image>



 4. Execute command mvn -pl infra docker:build docker:start to see if image of your service is started.


